			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I havn't seen these, but if my information is correct<BR>
right clicking on the gauntlets produces the Vibrating <BR>
Hammer of Infuse.  Right Clicking on the hammer<BR>
produces Vibrating Gauntlets of Infuse.  Both are <BR>
pretty sweet cleric items.  Once the items have been<BR>
transmuted you can switch between cleric hammer<BR>
and cleric gloves but you cant go back too the original.<BR>
<BR>
The bit I'm not sure about is the original change.  Its<BR>
third hand info but I know the cleric items are right.<BR>
<BR>
This could turn out to be complete BS, but reading the<BR>
posts above almost none of them have a clue apart <BR>
from they drop of Venril Sathir.<BR>
<BR>
Venril Sathir drops the legs for every class with a set of<BR>
class specific kunark armour, a staff for wizards, a <BR>
couple of ranger/druid quest items, and he has a rare<BR>
drop or two like these gloves.  Or at least thats what<BR>
he was dropping a month ago.<BR>
<BR>
Khain
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
